%20for%20so%20many%20reasons%20that%20I%20feel%20like%20help%20you%20in%20postpartum%2C%20specifically%20walkability%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20content%20creator%2C%20who%20goes%20by%20Alexis%20Kristiana%20online%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20so%20great%20to%20get%20out%20and%20move%2C%20connect%20with%20other%20parents%2C%20see%20other%20people%20outside.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alexis%20Adegoke%20and%20her%20children%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1f44b7b4fb977f3598387c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Adegoke%20family%20tried%20living%20in%20Texas.%3Cp%3EThalia%20Juarez%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20their%20family%20grew%2C%20though%2C%20a%20sense%20that%20they%20owed%20it%20to%20their%20children%20to%20give%20them%20a%20white-picket-fence%20life%20crept%20in.%20So%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20leave%20the%20city%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornian-regrets-moving-her-family-to-texas-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efor%20suburban%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20a%20decision%20they%20regretted%20almost%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223106275e-400a-43bd-af9d-2d69464a4da6%5C%22%3EGiving%20suburban%20life%20a%20try%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAdegoke%20spent%20most%20of%20her%20childhood%20in%20Dallas%2C%20where%20her%20family%20still%20lives.%20As%20she%20was%20raising%20her%20children%20in%20New%20York%2C%20she%20started%20to%20feel%20guilty%20that%20they%20didn't%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-lives-in-tiny-house-outside-new-orleans-saves-money-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebigger%20house%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20the%20green%20space%20she%20had%20growing%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20the%20Adegokes%20were%20also%20considering%20having%20more%20children%2C%20but%20their%20Brooklyn%20two-bedroom%20apartment%20was%20already%20bursting%20at%20the%20seams.%20They%20shared%20a%20bedroom%20with%20their%20kids%2C%20so%20the%20second%20bedroom%20could%20be%20an%20office%20and%20play%20space.%20Adding%20a%20third%20child%20to%20the%20room%20sounded%20daunting.%20Friends%20of%20theirs%20in%20New%20York%20also%20didn't%20think%20they%20had%20the%20space%20or%20resources%20to%20have%20more%20kids%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20just%20start%20to%20believe%20all%20of%20that%2C%20and%20that's%20why%20we%20started%20to%20look%20in%20Texas%2C%26quot%3B%20Adegoke%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20moved%20to%20Dallas%20in%20June%202022%20and%20bought%20a%20four-bedroom%2C%20two-bathroom%20house%20that%20was%20a%20little%20over%202%2C000%20square%20feet%20%E2%80%94%20an%20upgrade%20that%20%26quot%3Bfelt%20really%20big%26quot%3B%20to%20them%20compared%20to%20their%20two-bedroom%20apartment%2C%20Adegoke%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-and-husband-built-mom-tiny-home-on-their-property-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELife%20in%20Texas%3C%2Fa%3E%20worked%20for%20the%20family%20at%20first.%20Adegoke%20said%20they%20%26quot%3Bwere%20in%20a%20honeymoon%20phase%26quot%3B%20after%20they%20moved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kids%20playing%20in%20an%20apartment.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1f44062ab5f9757add841e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThey%20liked%20some%20things%20about%20their%20life%20in%20Texas.%3Cp%3EThalia%20Juarez%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20main%20thing%20we%20really%20loved%20was%20having%20the%20village%20and%20the%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BAs%20parents%2C%20we%20needed%20that%20separation%2C%20date%20nights%2C%20and%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20things%20for%20ourselves.%20My%20mom%20helped%20us%20out%20a%20lot%20with%20the%20kids%2C%20so%20that%20was%20really%20helpful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20months%2C%20however%2C%20they%20missed%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2241b2bcfa-0c60-4903-9108-eff0410a90e9%5C%22%3ELonging%20for%20city%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20about%20living%20in%20Texas%20that%20was%20fun%2C%20such%20as%20being%20near%20family%20and%20having%20more%20space%2C%20Adegoke%20said%20they%20knew%20within%20a%20year%20it%20wasn't%20right%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdegoke%20got%20pregnant%20with%20her%20third%20child%20shortly%20after%20the%20move.%20She%20said%20she%20had%20a%20harder%20time%20being%20pregnant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultigenerational-living-build-wealth-elder-care-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20suburbs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20feeling%20isolated%20because%20she%20couldn't%20just%20walk%20down%20the%20street%20or%20take%20a%20train%20to%20see%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Adegokes%20were%20also%20frustrated%20by%20having%20to%20drive%20everywhere.%20Their%20kids%20also%20missed%20seeing%20people%20walking%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20first%20moved%20there%2C%20our%20oldest%20would%20actually%20cry%20and%20ask%20us%2C%20'Why%20can't%20we%20walk%3F%20I%20want%20to%20walk%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20he%20would%20always%20ask%2C%20'Where%20are%20people%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdegoke%20said%20her%20husband%2C%20who%20works%20in%20the%20music%20industry%2C%20was%20missing%20out%20on%20work%20opportunities%20because%20he%20wasn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-grad-parents-pay-nyc-rent-cant-find-a-job-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20city.%3C%2Fa%3E%20She%20also%20realized%20that%2C%20to%20raise%20happy%20children%2C%20it%20was%20important%20for%20her%20to%20be%20happy%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20she%20wasn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg