1%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThey%20love%20being%20back%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3EThalia%20Juarez%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20feel%20like%20living%20in%20New%20York%20with%20kids%20is%20stressful%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20from%20a%20kid's%20point%20of%20view%2C%20they're%20having%20so%20much%20fun.%20They're%20scooting%20around.%20They're%20looking%20at%20cool%20stuff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdegoke%20said%20they've%20been%20exploring%20destinations%20they%20spotted%20in%20a%20National%20Geographic%20book%20for%20kids%20about%20New%20York%2C%20and%20her%20children%20have%20been%20loving%20checking%20places%20off%20their%20list.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20five%20of%20them%20are%20making%20New%20York%20their%20own%2C%20even%20her%20husband%2C%20who's%20taking%20advantage%20of%20being%20back%20in%20a%20hub%20for%20the%20music%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247f3e154-e707-4d9d-bf7c-ad45855b31c6%5C%22%3EA%20happier%20parent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Adegoke%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20benefits%20of%20being%20back%20in%20the%20city%20is%20that%20it's%20helped%20her%20connect%20with%20herself%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-new-york-city-miami-back-got-too-expensive-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eliving%20in%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20given%20her%20more%20time%20to%20recharge%2C%20whether%20that's%20by%20walking%20to%20a%20massage%20or%20meeting%20up%20with%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20it's%20been%20a%20huge%20shift%2C%26quot%3B%20Adegoke%20said%20of%20being%20back%20in%20the%20city.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20just%20so%20much%20happier%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alexis%20Adegoke%20and%20her%20husband%20in%20NYC.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1f4369b4fb977f3598386a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlexis%20Adegoke%20says%20she%20is%20happier%20as%20a%20parent%20in%20New%20York.%3Cp%3EThalia%20Juarez%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20feels%20less%20isolated%20than%20she%20did%20in%20the%20suburbs%20because%20people%20are%20everywhere%2C%20and%20she's%20feeling%20more%20kinship%20with%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-austin-texas-to-new-york-city-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20%3C%2Fa%3Emoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20part%20of%20the%20move%20for%20Adegoke%2C%20though%2C%20is%20seeing%20her%20whole%20family%20experience%20the%20joys%20of%20New%20York%2C%20from%20exploring%20new%20places%20around%20the%20city%20to%20spending%20time%20with%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20day%20is%20like%20an%20adventure%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-downsized-dallas-texas-house-nyc-apartment-happier-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780504735000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1f4d0b2ab5f9757add8466%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-downsized-dallas-texas-house-nyc-apartment-happier-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Alexis%20Adegoke%20thought%20raising%20her%20family%20would%20be%20easier%20in%20Texas.%20Instead%2C%20she's%20happier%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20even%20though%20it's%20more%20expensive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sgrindell%40businessinsider.com%20(Samantha%20Grindell%20Pettyjohn)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Transgender%20US%20troops%20can%20continue%20serving%20for%20now%2C%20in%20a%20major%20reversal%20for%20Trump%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Transgender%20troops%20who%20sued%20to%20block%20their%20separation%20from%20the%20US%20military%20won%20a%20legal%20victory%20at%20a%20federal%20appeals%20court%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20continue%20serving.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2037a12ab5f9757add86e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221325%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETransgender%20troops%20who%20sued%20to%20block%20their%20separation%20from%20the%20US%20military%20won%20a%20legal%20victory%20at%20a%20federal%20appeals%20court%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20continue%20serving.%3Cp%3EBill%20Clark%2FCQ%20Roll%20Call%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20majority%20of%20a%20three-judge%20panel%20found%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20trans%20ban%20was%20%26quot%3Barbitrary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20federal%20appeals%20court's%20decision%20allows%2028%20transgender%20troops%20to%20continue%20serving.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20of%20the%204%2C200%20transgender%20troops%20have%20quit%20after%20the%20new%20policies%20and%20heated%20rhetoric.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20appeals%20court%20ruled%20Monday%20that%20the%20Pentagon's%20policy%20to%20kick%20out%20transgender%20troops%20was%20illegal%2C%20halting%20the%20administration%20from%20removing%20more%20than%20two%20dozen%20transgender%20service%20members%20who%20have%20sued%20the%20Pentagon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20majority%20of%20the%20three-judge%20panel%20of%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20Circuit%20found%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20efforts%20to%20bar%20transgender%20troops%20were%20%26quot%3Barbitrary%26quot%3B%20and%20based%20on%20animus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20applies%20to%2028%20plaintiffs%20who%20filed%20suit%20last%20year.%20The%20decision%20is%20a%20major%20reversal%20for%20the%20Trump%20administration%20and%20allows%20those%20transgender%20troops%20to%20continue%20serving%2C%20though%20the%20military%20can%20continue%20to%20prohibit%20transgender%20recruits%20from%20joining.%20In%20a%202-1%20decision%2C%20the%20court's%20majority%20found%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20rhetoric%20and%20policy%20vilified%20transgender%20people%20and%20violated%20their%20rights%20to%20equal%20protection%20under%20the%20law%2C%20but%20legal%20experts%20cautioned%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20may%20be%20less%20sympathetic%20to%20these%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20moved%20quickly%20after%20taking%20office%20to%20bar%20transgender%20troops%20from%20service%20through%20an%20executive%20order%20that%20declared%20transgender%20identity%20incompatible%20%26quot%3Bwith%20a%20soldier's%20commitment%20to%20an%20honorable%2C%20truthful%2C%20and%20disciplined%20lifestyle.%26quot%3B%20Defense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20has%20repeatedly%20highlighted%20one%20of%20his%20accomplishments%20as%20%26quot%3Bno%20more%20dudes%20in%20dresses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20litigation%2C%20the%20government%20has%20not%20attempted%20to%20defend%20or%20provide%20any%20factual%20basis%20for%20these%20disparaging%20characterizations%20of%20American%20citizens%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20majority%20opinion%20said.%20%26quot%3BIndeed%2C%20the%20government%20has%20not%20contested%20that%20the%20Plaintiff-Appellees%20who%20are%20currently%20serving%20(and%20who%20have%20collectively%20earned%20more%20than%2080%20commendations)%20have%20served%20honorably%20and%20pose%20no%20threat%20to%20national%20security%2C%20even%20though%20they%20happen%20to%20be%20transgender.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20policy%20violated%20equal%20protection%20because%20it%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bunadulterated%20expression%20of%20animus%26quot%3B%20and%20reflected%20a%20%26quot%3Bbare%20...%20desire%20to%20harm%20a%20politically%20unpopular%20group%2C%26quot%3B%20Judge%20Robert%20Wilkins%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Justin%20Walker%20noted%20in%20his%20dissenting%20opinion%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20allowed%20the%20military%20to%20%26quot%3Bdeprive%20its%20members%20of%20rights%20that%20the%20Constitution%20may%20well%20guarantee%20to%20civilians%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20he%20dissented%20in%20part%20because%20%26quot%3Bthe%20plaintiffs%20are%20service%20members%20not%20civilians%2C%20and%20because%20we%20are%20judges%20not%20generals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20neither%20the%20expertise%20nor%20the%20authority%20to%20decide%20whether%20the%20military%20can%20exclude%20the%20plaintiffs%20from%20its%20ranks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Constitution%20assigns%20that%20authority%20to%20Congress%20and%20the%20Commander%20in%20Chief.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20referred%20Business%20Insider%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20when%20asked%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22397b93e3-d579-434d-86ca-94899164e908%5C%22%3E'The%20damage%20is%20already%20done'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20member%20of%20the%20US%20military%20outside%20a%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20courthouse%2C%20where%20a%20February%202025%20hearing%20was%20held%20over%20transgender%20troops'%20lawsuit%20seeking%20to%20block%20their%20separation.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a203e6e2ab5f9757add872b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20member%20of%20the%20US%20military%20outside%20a%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20courthouse%2C%20where%20a%20February%202025%20hearing%20was%20held%20on%20transgender%20troops'%20lawsuit%20seeking%20to%20block%20their%20separation.%3Cp%3EJim%20WATSON%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20is%20likely%20to%20appeal%20the%20decision%2C%20said%20Franklin%20Rosenblatt%2C%20a%20retired%20Army%20JAG%20officer%20and%20president%20of%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Military%20Justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20evidentiary%20record%20they%20have%20developed%20to%20show%20that%20by%20allowing%20trans%20people%20to%20serve%20in%20the%20military%2C%20that%20that's%20going%20to%20erode%20our%20national%20security%20somehow%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenblatt%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20based%20on%20national%20security%20as%20window%20dressing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20otherwise%20all%20this%20is%20really%20based%20on%20is%20discrimination%20against%20a%20politically%20unpopular%20class%20of%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20ruling%2C%20for%20many%20transgender%20troops%20%26quot%3Bthe%20damage%20is%20already%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rachel%20VanLandingham%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Southwestern%20Law%20School%20and%20a%20retired%20Air%20Force%20JAG%20officer.%20Many%20transgender%20service%20members%20have%20already%20left%20the%20military%2C%20opting%20to%20take%20what%20was%20characterized%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bvoluntary%26quot%3B%20separation%20rather%20than%20face%20discharge%20boards%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMilitary%20officials%20estimated%20in%20May%202025%20that%20around%201%2C000%20troops%20had%20identified%20themselves%20as%20transgender%20to%20begin%20their%20separation%20process.%20The%20Pentagon%20has%20estimated%20that%20there%20are%20about%204%2C200%20transgender%20troops%2C%20though%20one%202014%20estimate%20from%20the%20University%20of%20California%20Los%20Angeles%20School%20of%20Law%20put%20that%20figure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwilliamsinstitute.law.ucla.edu%2Fpublications%2Ftrans-military-service-us%2F%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclose%20to%2015%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20rational%20relation%20to%20good%20order%20and%20discipline%2C%26quot%3B%20VanLandingham%20said%20of%20the%20administration's%20justification%20for%20removing%20transgender%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20still%20has%20several%20steps%20before%20it%20could%20reach%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20VanLandingham%20said%2C%20including%20further%20proceedings%20in%20the%20lower%20courts%20and%20potential%20appeals.%20She%20expressed%20doubt%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20ultimately%20uphold%20the%20ruling%20in%20favor%20of%20transgender%20troops%2C%20calling%20such%20an%20outcome%20%26quot%3Bwishful%20thinking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftransgender-us-troops-can-continue-serving-for-now-court-rules-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780504682000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a203ea32e5a80cfe0502be9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftransgender-us-troops-can-continue-serving-for-now-court-rules-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20appeals%20court%20ruled%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20failed%20to%20show%20that%20transgender%20troops%20harm%20national%20security.%20It%20may%20not%20be%20the%20final%20word%20on%20their%20careers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kbaker%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A95%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sam%20Altman%20says%20OpenAI's%20top%20token%20spender%20uses%20100%20billion%20tokens%20a%20month%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they're%20not%20even%20the%20world%20leader%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman%20speaks%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69d51970f36fd1a78c0516a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESam%20Altman%20said%20that%20OpenAI's%20top%20token%20spender%20goes%20through%20100%20billion%20in%20a%20month.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESam%20Altman%20said%20that%2C%20within%20OpenAI%2C%20the%20top%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoken-reckoning-amazon-uber-reassess-ai-investments-2026-6%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etoken%20spender%3C%2Fa%3E%20goes%20through%20100%20billion%20tokens%20a%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESomebody%20outside%20OpenAI%20goes%20through%20more%20than%20that%20100%20billion%2C%20which%20Altman%20called%20a%20personal%20%26quot%3Bembarrassment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAltman%20recognized%20that%20token%20budgeting%20has%20recently%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20issue%26quot%3B%20for%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20employees%20are%20spending%20tokens%20on%20tokens%20on%20tokens.%20And%20yet%20it's%20someone%20outside%20the%20company%20who%20is%20spending%20the%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20lab's%20employees%20are%20known%20for%20their%20high%20AI%20spending.%20Peter%20Steinberger%2C%20the%20creator%20of%20OpenClaw%2C%20once%20spent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenclaw-peter-steinberger-ai-token-bill-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241.3%20million%20worth%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20tokens%20in%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20Tuesday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fbusiness%2Fintelligence-at-work%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenterprise%20event%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20talked%20about%20the%20company's%20highest%20token%20spender.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20and%20a%20half%20years%20ago%2C%20OpenAI's%20top%20token%20burner%20went%20through%20100%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20Altman%20said.%20That%20was%20%26quot%3Bvery%20likely%20the%20token%20leader%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%206.5%20years%20later%2C%20that%20is%20about%20the%20per%20capita%20average%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20the%20token%20leader%20at%20OpenAI%20uses%20about%20100%20billion%20tokens%20a%20month.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20the%20top%20token%20spender%20in%20the%20world%2C%20though.%20Altman%20said%20that%20the%20company%20found%20someone%20outside%20the%20company%20who%20spent%20more%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0something%20he%20called%20a%20personal%20%26quot%3Bembarrassment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20has%20a%20culture%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftokenmaxxing-ai-token-leaderboards-debate-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etoken%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company%20reportedly%20has%20a%20token%20leaderboard%2C%20and%20employees%20sometimes%20flex%20their%20high%20totals%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Frealchillben%2Fstatus%2F2052460518494069013%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20X%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20helps%2C%20of%20course%2C%20that%20OpenAI%20also%20sells%20the%20tokens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20other%20examples%2C%20OpenAI%20employees%20seemed%20to%20spend%20even%20more%20than%20100%20billion%20tokens%20in%20a%20month.%20Steinberger's%20screenshot%20showed%20603%20billion%20tokens%20spent%20in%2030%20days.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2026%2F03%2F20%2Ftechnology%2Ftokenmaxxing-ai-agents.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20one%20OpenAI%20employee%20spent%20210%20billion%20tokens%20in%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20OpenAI%20unleashes%20its%20tokens%2C%20other%20companies%20are%20tightening%20up.%20Amazon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-coo-andrew-macdonald-ai-token-spending-harder-justify-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshut%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20token%20leaderboard%2C%20and%20Uber%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2026-06-02%2Fuber-caps-usage-of-ai-tools-like-claude-code-to-cut-costs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%3C%2Fa%3E%20set%20token%20caps%20after%20its%20COO%20said%20that%20the%20spending%20was%20becoming%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-coo-andrew-macdonald-ai-token-spending-harder-justify-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eharder%20to%20justify%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20panel%2C%20Altman%20referenced%20the%20meme%3A%20%26quot%3BMy%20company%20spent%20my%20entire%202026%20budget%20in%20Q1%2C%20can%20you%20make%20this%20more%20efficient%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20said%20the%20company%20was%20continuing%20to%20push%20its%20models%20and%20explore%20other%20ways%20to%20deliver%20%26quot%3Bmore%20value%20for%20less%20spend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20the%20cost%20question%20came%20up%20quite%20suddenly.%20At%20the%20beginning%20of%202026%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20issue%20never%20came%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20were%20totally%20happy%20with%20the%20amount%20they%20were%20spending%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20AI%20costs%20are%20%26quot%3Ba%20huge%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-top-token-spender-ai-costs-issue-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780504344000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a2040e72ab5f9757add8737%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-top-token-spender-ai-costs-issue-2026-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sam%20Altman%20said%20AI%20budgeting%20has%20recently%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20issue%26quot%3B%20for%20some%20companies%2C%20something%20that%20%26quot%3Bnever%20came%20up%26quot%3B%20earlier%20this%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hchandonnet%40insider.com%20(Henry%20Chandonnet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Four%20sentenced%20to%20death%20for%20ki